HEADWORD: Merozoite
<hw>Mer`o*zo"ite</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr.
<grk>me`ros</grk> part + Sporo<ets>zoa</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>A form of spore, usually elongate or falciform, and somewhat
amoeboid, produced by segmentation of the schizonts of certain Sporozoa,
as the malaria parasite.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>Webster 1913 Suppl.</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Merrily</ent>⟦br⟧
